\begin{remark}
    With sectoral historical TMs and macro-financial variables, we may compute sectoral regression parameters. Yet, this data cannot be found easily and a global approximation with the same sensitivity of TMs with respect to equity is a necessary proxy. We note that the carbon cost effect is sectoral. Therefore, we will finally obtain sectoral TMs related to carbon price trajectories, ceteris paribus. 
